HEADWORD: Rehibition
<hw>Re`hi*bi"tion</hw> <pr>(r?`h?*b?sh"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> + L. <ets>habere</ets> to have.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The returning of a thing purchased to the seller,
on the ground of defect or frand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rehibitory</ent>⟦br⟧
